    <h2>Why Annual Wood Heater Servicing Is Essential</h2>
    <p>Every fire leaves behind creosote — a tar-like residue that coats the inside of your flue pipe. Over a season of regular use, that buildup restricts airflow, reduces the efficiency of your heater, and creates a genuine fire risk. Creosote is highly flammable. A chimney fire caused by creosote ignition burns at temperatures that can damage the flue lining and spread to the structure of your home.</p>
    <p>Beyond fire risk, a dirty flue is the most common cause of smoke coming back into the room, poor draw, fires that won't stay alight, and a persistent burning smell in the house when the heater isn't running.</p>
    <p>Annual servicing removes the buildup before it reaches dangerous levels, keeps the heater running efficiently, and is a requirement under most home insurance policies for wood heater coverage to be valid.</p>

