    <h2>When Should You Get Your Wood Heater Serviced?</h2>
    <p>The best time is autumn — April through May — before the heating season starts. This means your heater is clean, inspected and ready to go when the cold arrives in late May. You also beat the winter rush, when booking availability tightens up significantly.</p>
    <p>If you've missed the autumn window and the heater is already running, you can still book mid-season — but don't leave it until the end of winter when buildup is at its worst and risk is highest.</p>
    <p>If the heater hasn't been serviced in more than a year, or you've moved into a home with an unknown service history, book before the next time you use it.</p>
  </section>

